      "span_text": "Iacovelli et al [CITATION_1] recently reported data from a cohort of patients who had received three lines of therapy, suggesting that the sequence of VEGF inhibitor followed by another VEGF inhibitor followed by a mechanistic target of rapamycin (mTOR) inhibitor may be associated with better survival compared with a sequence in which an mTOR inhibitor was sandwiched between two VEGF inhibitors.",
